[Small outbreaks and single cases of _Angiostrongylus cantonensis_ are seen regularly in communities where consumption of raw snails is regarded as a delicacy. The infection may be overwhelming and lethal. Eosinophilia is the key finding which should lead to suspicion of _A. cantonensis_. - Mod.EP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1ob5.]
